   Northern Rocky Mountain Science Center

   Welcome to the Northern Rocky Mountain Science Center (NRMSC), newly
   formed by the U.S. Geological Survey to conduct integrated,
   interdisciplinary research in support of natural resource management in
   the Northern Rocky Mountains.  Our Center is based at Bozeman, Montana,
   with field stations at West Glacier and Missoula, Montana.  Northern
   Rocky Mountain Science Center We work in collaboration with Federal and
   state agencies, Native American tribes, academic institutions, and
   organizations to produce and disseminate information needed to support
   natural resource management decisions.

   This website provides information including:
     * NRMSC news
     * More about NRMSC
     * Staff directory
     * NRMSC research ventures
     * NRMSC products currently available
     * NRMSC partners

   If you would like more information about our center, please contact our
   outreach coordinator, marilyn_r_blair@usgs.gov.

   Richard L. Jachowski, Ph.D.
   Center Director

